# Solidarity Posters

High-energy union-board filler posters (Keep-Calm structure, not pastiche). Route: `/tools/solidarity-poster`.

## Visual direction
- Structure: small lead-in → **huge stacked headline** → short closer
- Colours: Brand Kit primary / secondary / accent only
- Avoid: purple gradients, cream+terracotta, broadsheet/newspaper layouts
- Formats: letter (8.5×11) and tabloid (11×17); PNG + PDF via existing export helpers
- Footer: CTA (“Get support →”), support URL, optional QR (on by default)
- No member photos → no ConsentModal
- No union names in slogans or core UI — Brand Kit / seed only

## Layouts
1. **Stack** — full-bleed primary, centered type; BrandLogo + local label when branding on
2. **Split** — colour block + type; colours only (no lockup) so type stays dominant
3. **Banner** — thick accent bar + oversized word + CTA strip; BrandLogo in bar when branding on

## Local branding
Theme established when: onboarding complete, OR official/custom logo set, OR local number non-empty (`isBrandThemeEstablished`).

- Established → “Include local branding” defaults ON; Stack/Banner show prominent `BrandLogo` + local label
- Not established → toggle OFF; soft link to `/onboarding`; user may force branding on
- Always seed canvas colours from Brand Kit

## Slogan tone
Generic, punchy, solidarity-first. See `SOLIDARITY_SLOGANS` in `src/lib/constants/solidarity-slogans.ts`.
